E-G
) tubular-shaped and small sized, ca. 0.90 mm long; median lobe distinctly elongate, ca. 1/3 of basal bulbus length. Parameres symmetrical and thin, shorter than 1/3 of basal bulbus length. Internal sac (Fig. 14-1E) with well sclerotized structure, tubular-shaped, apical portion with two black and large spines.
